26/07/2004
ANKARA, Turkey -- Firefighters have contained a fire at a major oil refinery in southern Turkey, the company operating the facility said in a statement Sunday (25 July). The fire started in a 9,000-tonne diesel oil tank. The cause is still not known. No injuries were reported.
In other news, 14 people were killed and six were injured when a van collided with a train in western Turkey. A local governor said the driver of the van had tried to cross the railroad track while the gates at the crossing were down because of the approaching train. The victims, including five children, were returning from a wedding party. (AP, Reuters, CNNTurk, AFP - 26/07/04)
